{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775851456232,"sessionID":"ses_28701628affeS0qakidQlEC2g4","part":{"id":"prt_d78fec254001vt11VnzfLcmRae","messageID":"msg_d78feb003001sENGXfkitW7CHQ","sessionID":"ses_28701628affeS0qakidQlEC2g4","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_53658f64b4594232a638a8a1","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-013/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-013/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-013 — Redis 存储实现\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing Redis storage in `pkg/store`.\n6: \n7: ## Base Specifications\n8: \n9: - **AR**: AR-013\n10: - **Module**: `pkg/store`\n11: - **Language**: Go\n12: - **Size**: M\n13: - **Base Specs**: \n14:   - `deployment/client-go.md` — Kubernetes client for runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh API\n15:   - `session-store/design.md` — Session store design with Redis implementation details\n16:   - `session-store/spec.md` — Session store specification with requirements\n17: \n18: ---\n19: \n20: ## Background\n21: \n22: AR-012 defined the session store interface contract. This AR (AR-013) implements the Redis backend for that interface. The Redis implementation uses:\n23: - `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` as the client library\n24: - Sorted sets for expiry and last-activity indexing\n25: - Pipeline operations for atomic multi-command execution\n26: \n27: ---\n28: \n29: ## Requirement: Redis Store Struct\n30: \n31: ### Scenario: Redis store struct defined correctly\n32: \n33: **GIVEN** the `pkg/store` package  \n34: **WHEN** the Redis implementation is defined  \n35: **THEN** the `redisStore` struct contains:\n36: - `cli *redisv9.Client` — Redis client instance\n37: - `sessionPrefix string` — constant `\"session:\"`\n38: - `expiryIndexKey string` — constant `\"session:expiry\"`\n39: - `lastActivityIndexKey string` — constant `\"session:last_activity\"`\n40: \n41: ---\n42: \n43: ## Requirement: Redis Connection Configuration\n44: \n45: ### Scenario: Redis options built from environment\n46: \n47: **GIVEN** `REDIS_ADDR` is set to `\"localhost:6379\"`  \n48: **AND** `REDIS_PASSWORD` is set to `\"secret\"`  \n49: **WHEN** `makeRedisOptions()` is called  \n50: **THEN** it returns `&redisv9.Options{Addr: \"localhost:6379\", Password: \"secret\"}`\n51: \n52: ### Scenario: Redis connection uses go-redis/v9\n53: \n54: **GIVEN** valid Redis options  \n55: **WHEN** `redisv9.NewClient(options)` is called  \n56: **THEN** a connection is established to the Redis server\n57: \n58: ---\n59: \n60: ## Requirement: Redis Ping Operation\n61: \n62: ### Scenario: Redis ping issues PING command\n63: \n64: **GIVEN** a healthy Redis server  \n65: **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called on Redis store  \n66: **THEN** the implementation executes `cli.Ping(ctx)`  \n67: **AND** expects string response `\"PONG\"`\n68: \n69: ### Scenario: Redis ping fails on disconnected server\n70: \n71: **GIVEN** Redis server is unreachable  \n72: **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called  \n73: **THEN** error is returned indicating connection failure\n74: \n75: ---\n76: \n77: ## Requirement: Redis GetSandboxBySessionID\n78: \n79: ### Scenario: Redis GET returns sandbox JSON\n80: \n81: **GIVEN** a session key `session:abc` exists with valid JSON  \n82: **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"abc\")` is called  \n83: **THEN** the implementation executes `GET session:abc`  \n84: **AND** unmarshals the JSON into `*types.SandboxInfo`\n85: \n86: ### Scenario: Redis GET returns nil for missing key\n87: \n88: **GIVEN** no key `session:abc` exists  \n89: **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"abc\")` is called  \n90: **THEN** Redis returns `redis.Nil`  \n91: **AND** the method returns `ErrNotFound`\n92: \n93: ---\n94: \n95: ## Requirement: Redis StoreSandbox Atomicity\n96: \n97: ### Scenario: StoreSandbox uses pipeline for atomicity\n98: \n99: **GIVEN** a valid `SandboxInfo` with `SessionID` = `\"test-session\"`  \n100: **WHEN** `StoreSandbox` is called  \n101: **THEN** the implementation executes pipeline with:\n102: - `SETNX session:test-session <json>` — sets session if not exists\n103: - `ZADD session:expiry <score>` — score = `ExpiresAt.Unix()`\n104: - `ZADD session:last_activity <score>` — score = `time.Now().Unix()`\n105: \n106: ### Scenario: StoreSandbox pipeline fails on error\n107: \n108: **GIVEN** pipeline execution  \n109: **WHEN** any command in the pipeline returns an error  \n110: **THEN** the error is propagated to the caller\n111: \n112: ### Scenario: StoreSandbox rejects nil sandbox\n113: \n114: **GIVEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, nil)` is called  \n115: **WHEN** the method validates input  \n116: **THEN** error indicates sandbox is nil\n117: \n118: ### Scenario: StoreSandbox rejects zero ExpiresAt\n119: \n120: **GIVEN** a sandbox with `ExpiresAt` set to zero time  \n121: **WHEN** `StoreSandbox` validates the input  \n122: **THEN** error indicates invalid expiry\n123: \n124: ---\n125: \n126: ## Requirement: Redis UpdateSandbox\n127: \n128: ### Scenario: UpdateSandbox uses SET with XX flag\n129: \n130: **GIVEN** an existing session key `session:abc`  \n131: **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox` is called with updated data  \n132: **THEN** the implementation executes `SET session:abc <json> XX`  \n133: **AND** does NOT modify expiry or last-activity ZSETs\n134: \n135: ### Scenario: UpdateSandbox fails when key missing\n136: \n137: **GIVEN** no session key `session:abc` exists  \n138: **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called  \n139: **THEN** Redis SETXX returns false  \n140: **AND** error is returned indicating key does not exist\n141: \n142: ---\n143: \n144: ## Requirement: Redis DeleteSandboxBySessionID\n145: \n146: ### Scenario: DeleteSandbox removes all keys in pipeline\n147: \n148: **GIVEN** an existing session with all three keys  \n149: **WHEN** `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"abc\")` is called  \n150: **THEN** pipeline executes:\n151: - `DEL session:abc` — removes session key\n152: - `ZREM session:expiry abc` — removes from expiry index\n153: - `ZREM session:last_activity abc` — removes from activity index\n154: \n155: ### Scenario: DeleteSandbox succeeds for non-existent session\n156: \n157: **GIVEN** no session key `session:abc` exists  \n158: **WHEN** `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"abc\")` is called  \n159: **THEN** operation succeeds (DEL returns 0, ZREM returns 0)\n160: \n161: ---\n162: \n163: ## Requirement: Redis ListExpiredSandboxes\n164: \n165: ### Scenario: ListExpired uses ZRANGEBYSCORE\n166: \n167: **GIVEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, beforeTime, 10)` is called  \n168: **WHEN** the implementation queries the index  \n169: **THEN** it executes `ZRANGEBYSCORE session:expiry -inf {beforeTime.Unix()} LIMIT 0 10`  \n170: **AND** retrieves session IDs with expiry <= beforeTime\n171: \n172: ### Scenario: ListExpired with limit <= 0 returns nil\n173: \n174: **GIVEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, beforeTime, 0)` is called  \n175: **WHEN** executed  \n176: **THEN** returns `nil, nil`\n177: \n178: ### Scenario: ListExpired loads JSON for each session id\n179: \n180: **GIVEN** ZRANGEBYSCORE returns session IDs `[\"abc\", \"def\"]`  \n181: **WHEN** fetching sandbox data  \n182: **THEN** pipeline executes GET for each key `session:abc`, `session:def`  \n183: **AND** returns `[]*types.SandboxInfo` with found entries\n184: \n185: ---\n186: \n187: ## Requirement: Redis ListInactiveSandboxes\n188: \n189: ### Scenario: ListInactive uses last_activity index\n190: \n191: **GIVEN** `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, beforeTime, 10)` is called  \n192: **WHEN** the implementation queries the index  \n193: **THEN** it executes `ZRANGEBYSCORE session:last_activity -inf {beforeTime.Unix()} LIMIT 0 10`  \n194: **AND** retrieves session IDs with last activity <= beforeTime\n195: \n196: ### Scenario: ListInactive with limit <= 0 returns nil\n197: \n198: **GIVEN** `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, beforeTime, -1)` is called  \n199: **WHEN** executed  \n200: **THEN** returns `nil, nil`\n201: \n202: ---\n203: \n204: ## Requirement: Redis Orphan Key Handling\n205: \n206: ### Scenario: Orphan ZSET member is skipped\n207: \n208: **GIVEN** ZRANGEBYSCORE returns session ID `\"abc\"` but no `session:abc` key exists  \n209: **WHEN** `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs` processes the results  \n210: **THEN** that ID is omitted from the returned slice  \n211: **AND** the operation does not fail\n212: \n213: ---\n214: \n215: ## Requirement: Redis UpdateSessionLastActivity\n216: \n217: ### Scenario: UpdateSessionLastActivity verifies existence first\n218: \n219: **GIVEN** an existing session `session:abc`  \n220: **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"abc\", time.Now())` is called  \n221: **THEN** the implementation first verifies key exists via `GET session:abc`  \n222: **AND** then executes `ZADD session:last_activity abc <score>`\n223: \n224: ### Scenario: UpdateSessionLastActivity returns ErrNotFound for missing session\n225: \n226: **GIVEN** no session key `session:abc` exists  \n227: **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"abc\", time.Now())` is called  \n228: **THEN** after GET returns nil, `ErrNotFound` is returned\n229: \n230: ### Scenario: UpdateSessionLastActivity uses current time for zero timestamp\n231: \n232: **GIVEN** an existing session  \n233: **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"abc\", time.Time{})` is called  \n234: **THEN** `time.Now().Unix()` is used as the ZADD score\n235: \n236: ### Scenario: UpdateSessionLastActivity rejects empty session id\n237: \n238: **GIVEN** empty session id `\"\"`  \n239: **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity` is called  \n240: **THEN** error is returned\n241: \n242: ---\n243: \n244: ## Requirement: Redis Close Operation\n245: \n246: ### Scenario: Close disconnects Redis client\n247: \n248: **GIVEN** an open Redis connection  \n249: **WHEN** `Close()` is called  \n250: **THEN** `cli.Close()` is executed  \n251: **AND** returns any error from close\n252: \n253: ---\n254: \n255: ## Requirement: Redis ZSET Score Semantics\n256: \n257: ### Scenario: Expiry index score uses ExpiresAt\n258: \n259: **GIVEN** a sandbox with `ExpiresAt` = 1700000000  \n260: **WHEN** `StoreSandbox` is called  \n261: **THEN** the ZADD score for `session:expiry` is `float64(1700000000)`\n262: \n263: ### Scenario: Last activity score uses time.Now() on store\n264: \n265: **GIVEN** `StoreSandbox` is called at time T  \n266: **WHEN** the last activity index is updated  \n267: **THEN** ZADD score is `float64(T.Unix())`\n268: \n269: ### Scenario: UpdateSessionLastActivity uses provided timestamp\n270: \n271: **GIVEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity` called with `at` = 1700000100  \n272: **WHEN** the ZSET is updated  \n273: **THEN** score is `float64(1700000100)`\n274: \n275: ---\n276: \n277: ## Requirement: Redis Implementation Completeness\n278: \n279: ### Scenario: Redis implements full Store interface\n280: \n281: **GIVEN** Redis store instance  \n282: **WHEN** all Store interface methods are called  \n283: **THEN** all methods are implemented:\n284: - `Ping(ctx context.Context) error`\n285: - `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n286: - `StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error`\n287: - `UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error`\n288: - `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error`\n289: - `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n290: - `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n291: - `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error`\n292: - `Close() error`\n293: \n294: ---\n295: \n296: ## Acceptance Criteria\n297: \n298: - [ ] `redisStore` struct defined in `pkg/store/store_redis.go`\n299: - [ ] `makeRedisOptions` parses REDIS_ADDR and REDIS_PASSWORD\n300: - [ ] `Ping` issues PING and expects \"PONG\"\n301: - [ ] `GetSandboxBySessionID` uses GET and returns ErrNotFound for Nil\n302: - [ ] `StoreSandbox` uses pipeline with SETNX, ZADD expiry, ZADD last_activity\n303: - [ ] `StoreSandbox` validates nil sandbox and zero ExpiresAt\n304: - [ ] `UpdateSandbox` uses SET with XX flag\n305: - [ ] `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` uses pipeline with DEL and ZREM\n306: - [ ] `ListExpiredSandboxes` uses ZRANGEBYSCORE on session:expiry\n307: - [ ] `ListInactiveSandboxes` uses ZRANGEBYSCORE on session:last_activity\n308: - [ ] List operations return nil for limit <= 0\n309: - [ ] `UpdateSessionLastActivity` verifies key existence before ZADD\n310: - [ ] Orphan ZSET members handled gracefully\n311: - [ ] `Close` calls cli.Close()\n312: - [ ] All Redis-specific acceptance scenarios pass verification\n313: \n314: ---\n315: \n316: ## References\n317: \n318: - Delta Spec: `changes/AR-013/delta-spec.md`\n319: - Delta Spec: `changes/AR-012/delta-spec.md`\n320: - Base Spec: `deployment/client-go.md`\n321: - Base Spec: `session-store/design.md`\n322: - Base Spec: `session-store/spec.md`\n\n(End of file - total 322 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-013 — Redis 存储实现\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing Redis storage in `pkg/store`.\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-013\n- **Module**: `pkg/store`\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: M\n- **Base Specs**: \n  - `deployment/client-go.md` — Kubernetes client for runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh API\n  - `session-store/design.md` — Session store design with Redis implementation details\n  - `session-store/spec.md` — Session store specification with requirements\n\n---\n\n## Background","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-013/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775851456197,"end":1775851456229}}}}
